&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Specialist Nurses /Deputy Team Leaders – PACU/Recovery Room &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There are exciting opportunity have arisen, within Recovery Department and our planned new PACU unit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We currently have Full time 37.5hrs Band 6 Specialist Nurse/Deputy Team Leader vacancies for an ODP/ Qualified anaesthetic Nurse or Registered Nurse to join our friendly busy theatre team. These posts are mainly to cover our planned Ashford Theatres PACU unit but you may also need to work cross site as and when needed. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This role includes a commitment to a day / night rotation, Bank Holidays and weekend working and on-calls from home.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You should have an excellent all around knowledge and skill to cover advanced post anaesthetic care of the patients. Level 1/Level 2 Critical Care development training is either already obtained or willing to develop to effective management of patients out of hours. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must have a level of management skills including time management, prioritization and organizational skills and the ambition to develop themselves and others. You will need excellent verbal and written communication skills and a strong belief in providing the best patient centred care possible. You will be expected to help maintain high standards of practice and act as a role model to your team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You should be able to support the core values of the trust in promoting putting patients first, having personal responsibility, passion for excellence and take pride with the team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return we offer opportunities for training and development, access to NHS pensions, work perks, access to NHS discounts and flexible working options.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are interested in this position please contact Tom D’souza Matron Ashford Theatres and Day Surgery on 01784 884188 email tom.d’souza@nhs.net to discuss the post further or to arrange an informal visit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
